🆕 __Build Challenge__
:build_plate: Boy, we have a lot of stone! Bet you do too! Let’s get creative! And make it retro too! Gather all your stone and show everyone what you’ve got! Build your best stone sculpture in the 8-bit style!
:stone: Channel your inner Michaelangelo and create a stone statue, only this time in 8-bit!
:air: 
🗿**8 Bit Statue Challenge- November 7th to November 21st**
:air: 
:paper: __Guidelines:__
:earth: Must be built in Minecraft Earth
:loading: This should be a brand new build and not be something that you've already built
:stonecutter_mc_animated:  Build plate size will not matter & won't be a factor in judging
:animMining:Feel free to ask for advice pertaining to your build in #8-bit-statue-challenge  
:mob_of_me: All work must be done by one individual
:fast_parrot: Remember, this is for fun only
📌If it's a submission picture, please feel free to ask a moderator to pin it.

8-bit is an early computer hardware device or software program that is capable of transferring eight bits of data at the same time. For example, the Intel 8080 processor, which was one of the first widely used computer processors ran on an 8-bit architecture
NES and Genesis console era style graphics, '80s stuff
Original Legend of Zelda was 8 bit, but Link to the Past was 16 bit, for example
Super Mario Bros. 3 for NES is top-teir 8 bit, lots of lee-way for creativity
I think the correct term is “pixel art”, not “8-bit art”
There is something called the “8-bit color palette”, which means the color on each pixel is decided by 8 bits only, instead of 24 or 32 bit truecolor used on modern machines.
